name: MicroservicesECommerce
description: This project, written in .NET Core 7, represents the core of a microservices e-commerce system that utilizes the publish-subscribe pattern for communication between services. It uses RabbitMQ as a message broker and JWT for authentication and authorization, providing flexibility in distributed systems.

name: Hotel-Microservice-Application
description: A microservices-based hotel management system built with Spring Boot and Spring Cloud. Consists of three core services: Hotel, Rating, and User, each handling specific functionalities. Utilizes MongoDB for data storage and implements service discovery using Eureka Server.

name: aeroverve-auth-service

name: food-ordering-system
description: The project purpose is to research and build a Microservice system that is responsible for big business size, high load capacity, and fault tolerance by applying Hexagonal, Domain Driven Design, CQRS, Saga, and Outbox Pattern, etc with Apache Kafka at its core technology of message queue.

name: timezone-identifier
description: A microservice to deliver timezone for specified coordinate given a geographic latitude/longitude in EPSG:4326 coordinate reference system.

name: naming-server
description: The Eureka Naming Server is a component designed to facilitate service discovery and registration within a microservices architecture. In the context of a GitHub repository, it is a vital part of the system that enables dynamic identification and communication between individual microservices.

name: RESTful-API-in-LoopBack3
description: LoopBack is an award-winning, highly extensible, open-source Node. js and TypeScript framework based on Express. It enables you to quickly create APIs and microservices composed from backend systems such as databases and SOAP or REST services.
